      "ord/char operations achieve 69–75% of native ord/chr (acceptable for cross-layer calls)",
      "All functions stable at 2.00 MB peak memory throughout entire benchmark suite"
    ],
    "known_limitations": [
      "replace_char is ~9× slower than PHP strtr due to O(n*m) VM iteration vs hash-table lookup (documented)",
      "size_ascii is slower than strlen because strlen is O(1) (length cached in zval); snobol Text::size always does UTF-8 scan",
      "reverse_ascii is much slower than strrev because strrev is essentially memcpy; snobol reverse decodes UTF-8 codepoints",
      "Pattern-based replace/tokenize is 50–400× slower than PCRE on simple patterns — expected for an interpretive pattern VM",
      "dupl_100x is 68% of str_repeat due to memory allocation overhead in C→PHP string construction"
